}\n    } catch {}\n}\nOutput\n(no output)\n\nThinking process\nThe \"gateway\" matches in _chat 4.txt are mostly about \"gateway to growth\" (a Black Business Show event) and \"capital\" discussions - not the Getaway app. Let me search the more recent chat files (_chat 3 and _chat (1)) for specific Getaway API doc mentions. Also let me look for any PDFs that were created or modified recently that might be the API doc.\n\nLet me also try to search in all PDF files for \"Getaway\" or \"getaway\" content - the Python approach failed. Let me try a different method.\n\nActually, let me check - maybe the Getaway API doc is in the chat files itself. Let me search _chat 3.txt and _chat (1).txt more carefully. Let me also check if there's a PDF related to Getaway in the ANDIEKOBBIE-OME folder on the Desktop.\n\nLet me search the most relevant recent chat files for the API doc and check for Getaway in the ANDIEKOBBIE folder:\n\n\nThought 2 time(s), Ran 5 command(s)\n\nTerminal\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\Downloads\\_chat 3.txt\" -E...\nTerminal\nInput\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\Downloads\\_chat 3.txt\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object {\n    $content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $lines.Length; $i++) {\n        if ($lines[$i] -match \"getaway|Getaway|Fizzy|FIZZY|Fifalou\") {\n            $snippet = $lines[$i].Substring(0, [Math]::Min(400, $lines[$i].Length))\n            \"[Line $i]: $snippet\"\n        }\n    }\n}\nOutput\n(no output)\n\nTerminal\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\Desktop\\ANDIEKOBBIE-OME\" ...\nTerminal\nInput\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\Desktop\\ANDIEKOBBIE-OME\" -Directory -Depth 1 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName | Select-Object -First 30\nOutput\nFullName                                                         \n--------                                                         \nC:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Deskto